    "department": "Operations",
    "description": "Replit is the agentic software creation platform that enables anyone to build applications using natural language. With millions of users worldwide, Replit is democratizing software development by removing traditional barriers to application creation.\n\nAbout the role\n\nWe are looking for a highly capable Executive Assistant to support our Chief Revenue Officer (CRO) and Chief Marketing Officer (CMO) at Replit. This role is ideal for an experienced EA who is ready to take on rapid organizational growth and act as a strategic partner to senior leaders.\n\nYou will manage complex schedules, support cross-functional initiatives, and help drive operational excellence across the Sales and Marketing organizations.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nExecutive \u0026 Operational Support\n\n - Provide high-quality executive support to the CRO and CMO, including complex calendar management, meeting coordination, travel planning, and expense management.\n\n - Anticipate needs and proactively flag conflicts, risks, and opportunities related to executive priorities.\n\n - Prepare meeting agendas, briefing materials, notes, and follow-ups to ensure meetings are productive and outcomes are clearly tracked.\n\nProject \u0026 Process Ownership\n\n - Support and manage SKOs and QBRs\n\n - Apply Replit’s best practices, tools, and workflows to complete projects with high accuracy and reliability.\n\n - Identify opportunities to improve processes, documentation, or workflows, and take action in partnership with your manager.\n\nCross-Functional Collaboration\n\n - Act as a strong thought partner to Sales, Marketing, and Partnerships\n\n - Work closely with EAs, Chiefs of Staff, and functional leaders to solve problems as they arise.\n\n - Seek out diverse perspectives and collaborate with the right stakeholders to move work forward efficiently.\n\nCommunication \u0026 Facilitation\n\n - Offer timely, thoughtful feedback to collaborators and stakeholders.\n\n - Represent the CRO and CMO with professionalism, discretion, and strong judgment.\n\nRequired Skills \u0026 Experience\n\n - 4+ years of experience as an Executive Assistant or in a similar administrative/operations role supporting senior leaders\n\n - Experience planning and executing events end to end\n\n - Strong working knowledge of core tools (e.g., Google Workspace, Slack, Notion) and the ability to apply them in workflows\n\n - Ability to work on complex tasks and well-defined projects that require analysis and sound judgment\n\n - Excellent organizational, communication, and time-management skills.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n - Prior experience supporting Go-To-Market organizations\n\n - Prior experience supporting two executives simultaneously with overlapping priorities\n\n - Comfortable creating and editing slide decks with strong visual hierarchy, clean formatting, and attention to detail; able to apply existing brand or design guidelines effectively\n\nThis is a full-time role that can be held from our Foster City, CA office. The role has an in-office requirement of Monday, Wednesday, and Friday.\n\nFull-Time Employee Benefits Include:\n\n💰 Competitive Salary \u0026 Equity\n\n💹 401(k) Program with a 4% match\n\n⚕️ Health, Dental, Vision and Life Insurance\n\n🩼 Short Term and Long Term Disability\n\n🚼 Paid Parental, Medical, Caregiver Leave\n\n🚗 Commuter Benefits\n\n📱 Monthly Wellness Stipend\n\n🧑‍💻 Autonomous Work Environment\n\n🖥 In Office Set-Up Reimbursement\n\n🏝 Flexible Time Off (FTO) + Holidays\n\n🚀 Quarterly Team Gatherings\n\n☕ In Office Amenities\n\nWant to learn more about what we are up to?\n\n - Meet the Replit Agent https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IYiVPrxY8-Y\n\n - Replit: Make an app for that https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4zd9hzngFwY\n\n - Replit Blog https://blog.replit.com/\n\n - Amjad TED Talk https://youtu.be/kCudFI4tcpg?si=l4ViCejV_f2RZkDi\n\nInterviewing + Culture at Replit\n\n - Operating Principles https://blog.replit.com/operating-principles\n\n - Reasons not to work at Replit https://blog.replit.com/reasons-not-to-join-replit\n\nTo achieve our mission of making programming more accessible around the world, we need our team to be representative of the world. We welcome your unique perspective and experiences in shaping this product. We encourage people from all kinds of backgrounds to apply, including and especially candidates from underrepresented and non-traditional backgrounds.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
